# Release Tag Deploy Workflow

- Do feature work on `agent/YYYY-MM-DD-<short-slug>` branches from `main`.
- Commit and push work to the agent branch while it is in progress.
- Do not deploy from ordinary `main` pushes. Cloudflare deployment is triggered by semantic version tags matching `vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`.
- When the user explicitly asks to merge/release the completed work, merge the branch into `main`, choose the next semantic version, create the tag from the updated `main`, then push `main` and the tag.
- Pick `patch` for fixes/small changes, `minor` for new user-visible functionality, and `major` for breaking changes.
- Never merge to `main` or create/push release tags unless the user explicitly asks for that release step.
